# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NUS shuttle (uNivUS / ConnectX FMS) configuration
#
# This repo is PUBLIC and intentionally ships NO reverse-engineered values.
# Every variable below is REQUIRED and has no baked-in default — the app and the
# scraper both fail loudly if one is missing. Copy this file to `.env`, fill in
# the values, and keep `.env` out of git (it already is, via .gitignore).
#
# Where they're used:
#   - the web app   -> set in Vercel (Project → Settings → Environment Variables)
#   - the scraper   -> set as GitHub Actions repository secrets
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Auth host for the uNivUS public access-token + bus-widget init-data flow.
NEXTBUS_AUTH_BASE=""

# ConnectX FMS base URL that serves the shuttle endpoints.
NEXTBUS_FMS_BASE=""

# uNivUS app version string sent during auth.
NEXTBUS_APP_VERSION=""

# uNivUS app API keys (sent as X-HTD-API / X-APP-API headers during auth).
NEXTBUS_HTD_API=""
NEXTBUS_APP_API=""

# FMS tenant identifiers. Without these the endpoints fail:
#   - ShuttleService                              needs NEXTBUS_FMS_SERVICE_ID
#   - BusStops / ServiceDescription / PickupPoint needs NEXTBUS_FMS_TENANT_CODE
NEXTBUS_FMS_SERVICE_ID=""
NEXTBUS_FMS_TENANT_CODE=""

# OPTIONAL: the app's "secure" Dio request headers. The server does NOT require
# them, so you can leave these blank; they're attached only when set.
# NEXTBUS_REQUESTED_BY=""
# NEXTBUS_SECURED_REQUEST=""
